<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,798,1147]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1050,1075]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks.</emphasis>
In females, corpus bursae is globular and directed posteriorly, length of signa is variable and almost one-third to one-half of the longitudinal length of corpus bursae, and the length of colliculum is 0.37–0.47 times as long as the antrum (n= 3). This species is newly reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[856,905,1123,1146]" name="Iran" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
